docs.text: godzilla is the ultimate culmination of the " who cares about plot " summer movie .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: a loose remake of the 1954 " classic " japanese monster movie , godzilla , king of the monsters ( which is itself pretty thin in the story department ) , roland emmerich and dean devlin's big-budget lizard-stomps-manhattan disaster flick has been written with the brain dead in mind .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the script isn't just " dumbed down , " it's lobotomized .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: godzilla lives and dies on special effects alone .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: presumably , the primary target group for this film is teenage boys , the demographic most likely to shell out $7 repeatedly to see the same images of monster-instigated carnage .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: that's not to say that females and other age groups are immune to the special effects seduction ; they're just not as readily susceptible .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: this is the third straight movie in a row where emmerich and devlin have demonstrated that a mastery of computer-generated visuals is far more important for making money than the ability to write and direct for actors .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: stargate was a financial success .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: independence day was a runaway hit .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: and , with godzilla already drowning in hype and merchandising tie-ins before it even opens , it's virtually guaranteed at least $100 million .

docs.text: godzilla isn't completely without merit , although it is close .

docs.text: with the possible exception of a mildly enjoyable car chase near the end , there isn't a sequence in this film that raises the pulse .

docs.text: even the scenes with dozens of aircraft attacking the monster are so devoid of tension and suspense that they are yawn-provoking .

docs.text: independence day may have been dumb , but it was full of " adrenaline moments " capable of getting the audience involved in the action .

docs.text: in this aspect of its production , as in so many others , godzilla is lacking .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: actually , part of the problem is that we're never sure who we're supposed to be rooting for : the green monster with an attitude or the paper-thin humans trying to stop him .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the plot , such as it is , can be summed up rather simply .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: after sinking a few ships and leaving some footprints on tropical islands , godzilla shows up in the big apple .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: he does some of the usual tourist things : stops by madison square garden , visits the chrysler building , goes on a walk through central park , and takes the subway .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: in the process , he knocks over a few buildings and steps on countless cabs , but he never has trouble with traffic jams .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: on hand to stop him is an elite u . s . army unit , led by a slightly less-arrogant-than-usual military man ( kevin dunn ) and a biologist named nick tatopoulos , who has a theory about godzilla .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: in his opinion , the big guy is actually a lizard grown to enormous proportions as a result of the radiation given off by french atomic bomb tests in the south pacific .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: in nick's words , godzilla is " a mutated aberration ? an incipient creature ? the first of its kind . "
docs.label: negative

docs.text: as luck would have it , nick's old girlfriend , audrey ( maria pitillo ) , is a reporter based at a new york tv station .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: along with her cameraman friend , animal ( hank azaria ) , she decides to follow nick around as he trails godzilla .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: then , just when the military has rejected nick's theory about why godzilla is in new york , a member of the french secret service ( jean reno ) recruits him for a special assignment .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: instead of stomping around tokyo this time , godzilla has chosen new york city .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: unfortunately , manhattan has been destroyed so many times in recent disaster movies ( independence day , deep impact , armageddon ) that it's becoming boring .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the whole tradition of monsters roaming around the city started with king kong , but the big ape was only about 30 feet tall .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: he could climb the empire state building .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: at ten times that height , godzilla would be more likely to knock it over .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: godzilla contains a few lame attempts at humor .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: there's an ongoing feud between animal and his wife that plays like sit-com material , an unfunny and repetitive gag about how no one can pronounce nick's last name properly , and a rather tame attack on film critics roger ebert and gene siskel .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: both of the popular personalities have alter egos in the film : " ebert , " the mayor of new york , is played by michael lerner , and " gene " ( lorry goldman ) is his campaign manager .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: ebert's re-election slogan is , not surprisingly , " thumbs up for new york . "
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the siskel/ebert stuff is amusing the first time it's used , but , after a while , it grows tiresome .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: and , although the " characters " don't serve any real purpose , they keep popping up .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: godzilla is saddled with an unimpressive cast .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: this is largely because emmerich doesn't want to risk a human performance upstaging his lizard .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: that's not to say that matthew broderick and jean reno aren't capable of good performances ( both have done their share of solid acting in the past ) , but they aren't a-list names .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: then again , considering the quality of the writing , even pacino and deniro would have been hard- pressed to shine .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: maria pitillo ( dear god ) plays the love interest and hank azaria ( great expectations ) is on hand to present what is supposed to be comic relief .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: ultimately , it doesn't really matter what i ( or any other critic , for that matter ) have to say about the movie .

docs.text: tristar has assumed that godzilla , like all self-proclaimed summer event motion pictures , is pretty much critic-proof .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it may also be word-of-mouth-proof .

docs.text: those who want to see the movie will see it no matter what i write or their friends say .

docs.text: so , when i go on record to assert that godzilla is one of the most idiotic blockbuster movies of all time , it's like spitting into the wind .
